<title>Underlying principles</title>

<p>There are five basic steps to implementing the technique:</p>
<p>1. decide on the task to be done</p>
<p>2. set the pomodoro (timer) to 25 minutes</p>
<p>3. work on the task until the timer rings; record with an X</p>
<p>4. take a short break (3-5 minutes)</p>
<p>5. every four "pomodori" take a longer break (15â€“30 minutes)</p>

